RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 1 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $ 15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIGHTENING ANNA lagged early, advanced quickly in the four path leaving the backstretch, took over at the head of the stretch, and drove clear. SPORTSCARR sat near the back of pack while three wide, was set down into the final turn, and edged away late for second. FROSTEDBIRD stalked three wide, moved up closer to challenge the lead, gained a short advantage, and lacked the closing response needed. BEAUGATTI attended the pace from between foes, and came up empty in the drive. MONEY MUNCHER tracked inside and failed to threaten. WOMANONTHEWARPATH contended the early pace from along the rail, and tired. JOCKEY OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the rider of SPORTSCARR against the rider of LIGHTENING ANNA alleging interference on the final turn was not allowed.

ENTRY.NAME: Money Muncher
ENTRY.OWNER: C and H Duggan Farms Ltd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 2 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $6,250.

CLAIM.OWNER: Salt River Holdings Inc and Viking Stables

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHARP DRESSED BEAU vied for the early lead outside of PERDITION, emerged the leader then showed the way through the backstretch, responded to looming threat from GIVE EM HECK BECK, and drove clear under handling. GIVE EM HECK BECK sat in striking position, chased hard on the final turn but was unable to stall the winner, was kept to steady handling holding on for the place. PERDITION vied inside then settled just off the pace, rallied into the stretch, and weakened late. HARD TO COME HOME was under a strong hold early then was in close quarters through the opening turn, chased in the last turn, and lacked a kick. CARSON'S LEGACY went three to four wide into the backstretch, and tired early. NORTH FORK trailed throughout.

ENTRY.OWNER: Dietz Lloyd Fernandez Stephanie and Kerredge Farm

ENTRY.NAME: Hard to Come Home

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SKIP'S ROCK quickly took command, led the field through the backstretch, moved clear into the stretch then was kept to a strong hand ride and held under late pressure. BIG HUG stalked three to four wide into the opening turn, was asked to quicken approaching the stretch, was gaining late, and missed. SUPER CARO rated off the pace, drove inside at the head of the stretch, and was outkicked. SINGING BELL sat just off the pace while three wide, and had nothing left in reserve late.

ENTRY.NAME: Super Caro
ENTRY.OWNER: Gorst Logan Gorst Gary O'Hagan Colleen and Poitras Racing Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 4 7 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS IN THEIR LAST THREE STARTS AND HAVE NOT WON A STARTER SINCE STARING FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS OR OPTIONAL CL AIMING $12,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MI REYNA contested the lead outside of GO MAMA, gained a short advantage nearing the stretch, and drew away. ADDYDIDIT stalked outside from the four path, moved up menacingly nearing the quarter pole, rallied through the stretch then edged clear. GO MAMA contended the pace from the rail, was unable to move on with the eventual winner and gave way. HENRY'S GAMBLE rated well of the pace inside, rallied into the stretch, and finished evenly. WITT'S TENNY TEN chased three to four wide and was unable to improve position. BOOTIFUL ROSE stumbled leaving, and showed a mild interest late. JOY IN GRACE lost position nearing the opening turn, chased and was not a factor.

ENTRY.OWNER: Danard Don B and Knight Don

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MAY 5 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Lesser Claiming Races For $6,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bre d Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXAMINER allowed to settle inside early, shifted out three to four wide at the head of the lane, overtook the lead, and won driving. WYE CROSS tracked three to four wide, swung out in the final turn, closed well late, and was along with time for second. DUNE D'ORO set for outside speed, led the field into the backstretch, responded to a challenge from BROWING ISLAND but was out-finished in the stretch. LITTLE CHICAGO sat mid-pack and bid belatedly. EXPLODE trailed the field early, lodged a bid into the far turn, and came up empty for the drive. BROWNING ISLAND fanned four wide into the backstretch, chased outside moving up alongside DUNE D'ORO, was unable to match strides with rival and gave way. DAD'S LEGACY hurried early then was outsprinted to the turn, chased three wide and tired. LAST RENEGADE saved ground and had no response when called upon.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: WIZARDOFMENLOPARK brushed leaving, gained closer order leaving the backstretch, found racing room inside, shifted out to the two path, and won driving. SIX SHOTS OF T attended the pace from the rail, inherited the lead entering the last turn, and was caught. TRAPEZE lacked a clear path leaving, chased leaving the backstretch, angled inside to the three path, and finished evenly for show. BORN ON FIRE lacked early speed, drove inside at the head of the stretch, and flattened. JOKERS R WILD raced at the back of the pack, drove three to four wide on the final turn, shifted inside, and improved position. NO MOR DISCO fanned four wide into the opening turn, dropped back through the backstretch, raced wide into the lane, and rallied mildly late. GWIZZ fanned three-wide, was unable to move on with SIX SHOTS OF T, drifted out at the head of the lane and faded. FAVORITE LIGHT attended the pace from between foes, and stopped in the final turn. RYE TOAST brushed leaving, chased hard while five wide, was pulled up, did not finish and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: RECIO'S SKYE sat in striking distance from the five path, moved up alongside WISH ON A STAR to challenge the lead, gained a narrow advantage and prevailed. WISH ON A STAR sat just off the pace in the two path, overtook the lead then responded to a challenge from RECIO'S SKYE into the stretch, lost the advantage, and finished second best. TENDER LOVE brushed leaving, trailed early, hustled through the far turn, rallied three wide earning show honors. SMOKIN JOY stalked inside, experienced traffic in the far turn, found seam into the lane and was out-finished for show. DUBD SAINT ANGEL chased five-wide through the backstretch, fanned four wide at the head of the lane, and yielded late stretch. ASHES TO ASHES saved early, chased three wide, and failed to threaten in the drive. BLAZING SUN sent for early speed outside, chased the pace from the three path, and wilted in the stretch. STARMA set the pace from just off the rail, and tired early. CHABI offered little.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY DOWNS RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 23000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOUR O SIX CREED tracked along the rail, gained closer order, shifted out to the three path at the head of the lane, and won going away. READYTOTAPNSING raced five wide into the opening turn, went in pursuit of the leader leaving the backstretch, gained a short lead, and was outkicked. H K RAPPER went three to four wide leaving the front side, advanced quickly into the final turn, dug in the final yards getting up late for show. DOUSEAWHATISEA rider lost his irons leaving the chute, regained control nearing the opening turn, opened up with good margins in the backstretch, was showing signs of tiring nearing the stretch, and gave way. ARGENTINA CRIES (IRE) stalked three to four wide into the opening turn, raced in closest pursuit, rallied three wide and was narrowly denied. KYSTONE reserved off the early pace in the three path, lodged a mild bid from the rail and flattened deep stretch. IT'S A FACT saved ground from the rail, dropped back, and showed a mild interest late. BIG BAD INTAGLIO lost ground in the opening turn, lodged a rail bid into the final turn and came up empty in drive. FLASHIN ACES trailed and passed tiring rivals. ALTITUDE was under a snug hold nearing the opening turn, and lacked a serious bid. ROUGH CUSTOMER flashed some early speed and was outrun.
